name: FSubmixEffectDelaySettings
doc:
FSubmixEffectDelaySettings
UStruct used to define user-exposed params for use with your effect.

MaximumDelayLength: Maximum possible length for a delay, in milliseconds. Changing this at runtime will reset the effect.
InterpolationTime: Number of milliseconds over which a tap will reach it's set length and gain. Smaller values are more responsive, while larger values will make pitching less dramatic.
DelayLength: Number of milliseconds of delay.  Caps at max delay at runtime.
